dismissalText.commentary: Younis Khan c & b Jarvis 81 (90b 6x4 1x6 99m) SR: 90

dismissalComment.html: another stunning return catch, and Pakistan are in a spot of strife here. It was in many ways a replay of Malik's dismissal - full ball, eliciting the drive to the left of the bowler, who reacted rapidly to tumble and pluck it low, with both hands this time, on his follow through. Younis seemed to be drawn into the shot early and couldn't keep it down. 300 too optimistic now?

dismissalText.commentary: Asad Shafiq st †Taibu b Price 51 (72b 3x4 1x6 103m) SR: 70.83

dismissalComment.html: appeal for stumping, and Shafiq could be in trouble. Flighted ball from Price, landed outside leg after passing Shafiq who was lured out of the crease for the flick. He missed, Taibu didn't collect it cleanly at first, but grabbed the rebound off his chest and removed the bails well on time. The umpire seems to have forgotten to signal a wide too.

headshotImage.caption: Imran Farhat player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Imran Farhat player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: Elton does the job. He's tied Farhat down with the tight lengths, and suddenly goes fuller, and I suspect, slightly slower. Farhat was too eager to drive, he seemed to be early on the shot and scooped it in the air towards cover, who tumbled forward to take a smart catch.

dismissalComment.html: Elton Chigumbura takes a blinder on the rebound! Zimbabwe's fielding continues to be a Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde show. Full ball on off stump, Malik got into the drive and hit it to the left of the bowler at shin-height. Elton reacted superbly on his follow through to pluck it low to his left as he skid and tumbled alongside it.

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Hafeez c Waller b Vitori 23 (21b 4x4 0x6 36m) SR: 109.52

dismissalComment.html: the radar is not with Zimbabwe, it is with Pakistan! Short from Vitori, angling into the batsman, and Hafeez responds with an imperious pull. It seemed set to sail towards the midwicket boundary, but hang on.. There was a man at deep midwicket. And Hafeez could not have picked him out more accurately if he had tried to.

dismissalText.commentary: Chamu Chibhabha c Younis Khan b Shoaib Malik 62 (88b 7x4 0x6 135m) SR: 70.45

dismissalComment.html: dismissal, soft as a baby's bottom. Chamu has chipped a friendly length ball on off stump against the turn, inside out, straight into the hands of cover standing in the circle. Zimbabwe are losing too many wickets too quickly.

dismissalText.long: c sub (Umar Akmal) b Yasir Shah
dismissalText.commentary: Vusi Sibanda c sub (Umar Akmal) b Yasir Shah 59 (76b 5x4 1x6 112m) SR: 77.63

dismissalComment.html: Sibanda commits suicide. He was looking good, and Zim aren't in a situation where they have to hit everything. He jumps out to this one, doesn't get to the flight but still tries to heave the loft over long-on. No luck, he finds the fielder in the deep and Yasir Shah has his first ODI wicket.

the in-form Taylor is gone. That's a cruel blow for Zim. Taylor tried to be innovative there, he was looking to guide a ball just outside off through to third man, manufacturing room as he set himself up beside the line. He couldn't get enough on it, and feathered it through to the keeper.
Elton has perished. Short ball again from Cheema, but no width this time. Elton went for the pull, and looped it off the top edge to deep midwicket. Zim sink further.

the stumps go for a walk around the Harare Sports Club. Straight, length ball, challenging Waller to go for the cross-batted heave. He does and misses. The stumps are messed up. So are Zimbabwe's hopes.

image.caption: Tatenda Taibu

dismissalComment.html: Younis Khan, take a bow! And they actually dropped this man from their team. He may be old, he may be close to the end of his career, but he's still among the fittest guys in this side. Short from Yasir, but he has the ability to skid along faster than you'd imagine. That's what spoiled Taibu's heaved sweep, but he should have still been safe. Someone forgot to tell Younis who zipped across to his right, dived full length and plucked it.

dismissalText.commentary: Kyle Jarvis b Mohammad Hafeez 6 (12b 0x4 0x6 11m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: Hafeez has the plot safely in his briefcase though. Flat ball aimed at the stumps, Jarvis misses the cut and timber meets leather.

commentTextItems.html: the last ball hurries through and Vitori can't connect with the pull. Pakistan take the series 3-0 and that's a well-deserved clean sweep.

commentPostTextItems.html: Misbah and the boys look a genuinely happy bunch as they come along to pose with the trophy. Well played Pakistan! Firdose's report has all the ebbs and flows of today's game. That winds up our coverage for the ODIs, but the T20s are round the corner. Do join us for them. On behalf of the gang at ESPNcricinfo, this is Nitin Sundar signing off. So long.

Younis, however, wins the Man of the Series award. "We had a tough series, the Zimbabweans gave us a tough time and I believe they will have a good team in the future. Before the series, the seniors sat together and hoped to deliver and show the way for the youngsters, and I am happy we could do that." He laughs when the T20s are mentioned! "If I am given the chance I will contribute again for my country," he says.

Cheema pips Younis Khan to pick up Man of the Match Award. Cheema thanks his family for his success in this series. "All the hard work I did in the last 10 years have borne fruit. The coach, captain and team have stood by me and I am thankful. I just tried to hit the right lengths, and it worked."

Misbah; "Good to see new boys coming in and performing. The main idea was to give a couple of youngsters chances, and win the series. We achieved that well. We were around 25-30 runs short, they bowled well in the last 7-8 overs. But happy with the way we bowled and fielded. There might be one-two changes to ensure we have the right balance for the Twenty20s."

Taylor: "There were too many dot-balls at the start which made it tough for people coming in. Good teams make it tough for you to build on a platform, and Pakistan played the better cricket today. Our bowlers showed good heart in the middle and end overs, but they came out and made it difficult for us."

Handshakes all around. Zimbabwe will look back at this game, and in fact this series, as an opportunity missed. The should have won the first game, and they were in a really solid position in this one when Taibu and Masakadza were going. Pakistan did their bit to bring the pressure on, credit to them.

commentTextItems.html: Vitori launches a full ball high over deep square leg and Shoaib Malik drops the tumbling catch. No harm done, a couple of runs taken.
flat ball on middle and leg, worked through the leg side.
tossed up to Vitori who lashes it to long-off for a single.

commentPreTextItems.html: Hafeez comes on for the final over.

commentTextItems.html: flat outside off, cut away through point for a couple. The game is officially out of Zim's reach unless Hafeez loses the plot in compelling manner.
Jarvis pushes another single down the ground. 35 needed off the last over. Where is Sobers? Where is Shastri? Where is Gibbs? Where is Yuvraj?

commentTextItems.html: Utseya drives down the ground for a single.
Jarvis backs away to a length ball angling in and works a single to deep square leg.
now the yorker aimed at the toes, Jarvis digs it out and Zim just can't get a boundary anywhere.
another slower ball, another complete miss as Jarvis plays well before the ball's arrival.
Utseya squeezes a single through the cover-point area as Sohail keeps it full.
back of a length outside off, Utseya guides it down to third man for a single.

commentTextItems.html: fuller ball this time, tailing in late and it is crunched off the inside edge through square leg.
short of a length outside off, Jarvis looks to cut and misses.
top-class slower ball that, Jarvis played his drive a year before the ball came. How did it miss the stumps?
Jarvis backs away and drives, but he misses the line completely.
another short ball from Tanvir, Utseya drops it to the leg side and they take the single.
no five-for for Cheema, he finishes with a full length ball on the pads that is nudged to the leg side for one.

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Hafeez c Waller b Vitori 23 (21b 4x4 0x6 36m) SR: 109.52

dismissalComment.html: the radar is not with Zimbabwe, it is with Pakistan! Short from Vitori, angling into the batsman, and Hafeez responds with an imperious pull. It seemed set to sail towards the midwicket boundary, but hang on.. There was a man at deep midwicket. And Hafeez could not have picked him out more accurately if he had tried to.

dismissalText.commentary: Imran Farhat c Chibhabha b Chigumbura 37 (45b 7x4 0x6 69m) SR: 82.22

dismissalComment.html: Elton does the job. He's tied Farhat down with the tight lengths, and suddenly goes fuller, and I suspect, slightly slower. Farhat was too eager to drive, he seemed to be early on the shot and scooped it in the air towards cover, who tumbled forward to take a smart catch.

dismissalText.commentary: Asad Shafiq st †Taibu b Price 51 (72b 3x4 1x6 103m) SR: 70.83

dismissalComment.html: appeal for stumping, and Shafiq could be in trouble. Flighted ball from Price, landed outside leg after passing Shafiq who was lured out of the crease for the flick. He missed, Taibu didn't collect it cleanly at first, but grabbed the rebound off his chest and removed the bails well on time. The umpire seems to have forgotten to signal a wide too.

headshotImage.caption: Shoaib Malik player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Shoaib Malik player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Shoaib Malik c & b Chigumbura 14 (14b 1x4 0x6 23m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: Elton Chigumbura takes a blinder on the rebound! Zimbabwe's fielding continues to be a Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde show. Full ball on off stump, Malik got into the drive and hit it to the left of the bowler at shin-height. Elton reacted superbly on his follow through to pluck it low to his left as he skid and tumbled alongside it.

headshotImage.caption: Kyle Jarvis player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Kyle Jarvis player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Kyle Jarvis player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Kyle Jarvis player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Younis Khan c & b Jarvis 81 (90b 6x4 1x6 99m) SR: 90

dismissalComment.html: another stunning return catch, and Pakistan are in a spot of strife here. It was in many ways a replay of Malik's dismissal - full ball, eliciting the drive to the left of the bowler, who reacted rapidly to tumble and pluck it low, with both hands this time, on his follow through. Younis seemed to be drawn into the shot early and couldn't keep it down. 300 too optimistic now?

dismissalText.long: c sub (Umar Akmal) b Yasir Shah
dismissalText.commentary: Vusi Sibanda c sub (Umar Akmal) b Yasir Shah 59 (76b 5x4 1x6 112m) SR: 77.63

dismissalComment.html: Sibanda commits suicide. He was looking good, and Zim aren't in a situation where they have to hit everything. He jumps out to this one, doesn't get to the flight but still tries to heave the loft over long-on. No luck, he finds the fielder in the deep and Yasir Shah has his first ODI wicket.

headshotImage.longCaption: Shoaib Malik player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.long: c Younis Khan b Shoaib Malik
dismissalText.commentary: Chamu Chibhabha c Younis Khan b Shoaib Malik 62 (88b 7x4 0x6 135m) SR: 70.45

dismissalComment.html: dismissal, soft as a baby's bottom. Chamu has chipped a friendly length ball on off stump against the turn, inside out, straight into the hands of cover standing in the circle. Zimbabwe are losing too many wickets too quickly.

dismissalText.commentary: Brendan Taylor c †Adnan Akmal b Aizaz Cheema 6 (14b 0x4 0x6 13m) SR: 42.85

dismissalComment.html: the in-form Taylor is gone. That's a cruel blow for Zim. Taylor tried to be innovative there, he was looking to guide a ball just outside off through to third man, manufacturing room as he set himself up beside the line. He couldn't get enough on it, and feathered it through to the keeper.

dismissalText.commentary: Hamilton Masakadza c Misbah-ul-Haq b Sohail Khan 21 (26b 0x4 1x6 43m) SR: 80.76

dismissalComment.html: Zimbabwe are disintegrating here, and it all down to inexperience. Slower ball from Sohail, Masakadza spotted it, but couldn't resist himself from pulling. Straight to Misbah at midwicket in the circle.

dismissalText.long: c Younis Khan b Yasir Shah
dismissalText.commentary: Tatenda Taibu c Younis Khan b Yasir Shah 27 (26b 2x4 1x6 29m) SR: 103.84

dismissalComment.html: Younis Khan, take a bow! And they actually dropped this man from their team. He may be old, he may be close to the end of his career, but he's still among the fittest guys in this side. Short from Yasir, but he has the ability to skid along faster than you'd imagine. That's what spoiled Taibu's heaved sweep, but he should have still been safe. Someone forgot to tell Younis who zipped across to his right, dived full length and plucked it.

dismissalText.commentary: Malcolm Waller b Aizaz Cheema 19 (18b 2x4 0x6 33m) SR: 105.55

dismissalComment.html: the stumps go for a walk around the Harare Sports Club. Straight, length ball, challenging Waller to go for the cross-batted heave. He does and misses. The stumps are messed up. So are Zimbabwe's hopes.

dismissalText.commentary: Elton Chigumbura c Asad Shafiq b Aizaz Cheema 9 (15b 1x4 0x6 19m) SR: 60

dismissalComment.html: Elton has perished. Short ball again from Cheema, but no width this time. Elton went for the pull, and looped it off the top edge to deep midwicket. Zim sink further.
